<br>
As you see, almost every character is someone you may have met at one point in the game.  The Razor's Edge officer roster is almost indentical to the one near Razor's disbanding.  Other characters, Lucan, Brother Jentry, Theron Rolius, etc. you can actually talk to or kill, depending on your mood and level, for they are actual NPCs.  Sir Bamible is one of the few characters created straight from my twisted imagination.  And Sylver and Emaus, Camille's parents?  Long ago Camille and I came to a new server called Vazaelle from a rather rabid server called Rallos Zek.  Our characters there?  Sylverdane Metalsmyth, a human mage with eyebrows that met in the middle (ala the old PoD graphic) and Emaus Spelldancer, fourth wizard to 50 when 50 was 'end game' and the best place to xp was the newbie guards at the Freeport gate before they got superhuman powers.  Riverdane existed on Rallos too, as a 36 level warrior, Riverdane Blackrazor.  You could imagine how well a pure melee did on a server where anyone within 4 levels of you could blow you away.  Such a long time ago, but felt like a fitting tribute to the characters we played before Vazaelle was born. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/leopa/misc/riverdane_animatedbanner.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skifksheyna>Skif kSheyna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 175<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/31/03 11:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=65>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wake</span><hr size=1> very nice river. good to hear freeport got cleaned up (never did like that city....) <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div s