</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=riverdane>Riverdane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 449<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/3/03 4:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=71>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Commentary on Wake</span><hr size=1> Aye, all of them are 65 at the present time.  Explaining levels is becoming a bigger and bigger bitch, especially with the whole Naggy Vox banishment thing.  I sat there looking at a blank computer screen for a good hour before I launched into writing that unbelievably difficult chapter where Whiz explains the theories of their imprisonment and the nature of the banishment.  Some lore I got from Sony's actual published and official map book, others I got from google searches and some, like why 53 plus can't enter the chambers, I had to make up from scratch.  I had a pounding headache when I was finished, and still have a feeling I may have to clean it up a bit when I get to the rewrite.<br>
<br>
Oh, speaking of which.  All three stories combined are now just ticking over 600 pages total.  I expect Wake has another 200 or so before it is done.  Since the plan is to release all three as one book, I will then be heading in add a rather longish prologue to Breathless, and then rewriting Breathless almost totally (in style, not content) and parts of the beginning of Breathe to match the style that Breathe took on sometime in the middle of it, and bring it all to the style that was throughout Wake.  Hopefully, not only will this clean the whole thing up, but also the Prologue will set down some givens, educating non-eq players and making it an enjoyable  read for someone that doesn't know what the hell a &quot;tank&quot; is or what a &quot;nuker&quot; may do.<br>
<br>
I hope...=p <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/leopa/misc/riverdane_animatedbanner.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rocsalt>Rocsalt</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/3/03 7:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=72>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Commentary on Wake</span><hr size=1> Everyone traveling in this story is level 65, each with their own set of aa's ranging from over 50 to over 250. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:comic sans ms;font-size:x-large;"><br>
